{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17490960","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17490960"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:25:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:25:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"786"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"786","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/786"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.35,0.55,0.04,0.04,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"786"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109625"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"786","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/786"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"786"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92015"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"160"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"2544"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"661"},{"type":"contributions","id":"1631"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16158"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41055"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42149"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43037"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109625","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/109625"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 27-year-old man sustains left-sided rib fractures and a fracture of his left shaft of femur in a motorcycle crash. Apart from some tenderness over his ribs, there is no evidence of serious chest injury on X-ray. Seven days after an open reduction and internal fixation of the fractured femur, he complains of sudden breathlessness and light-headedness. He had been making good post-operative progress up to this stage. On examination, his blood pressure is 110/80 mmHg, pulse 100/min, respiratory rate 24/min, oxygen saturation 91%, and temperature 37.8C. Both lung fields are clear on auscultation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fat embolus","Pulmonary embolus","Basal atelectasis","Pneumonia","Pneumothorax"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is likely suffering a post-operative pulmonary complication, as indicated by his sudden onset hypoxia, as well as tachypnoea, tachycardia and fever. The time to symptom presentation is often used to narrow down the differential diagnoses in the perioperative period. At one week post-op, the most likely diagnosis is \u003Cstrong\u003Epulmonary embolism\u003C/strong\u003E (PE) due to prolonged immobilisation following major surgery. Patients with PE often present with non-specific signs and can very rapidly decline, so early recognition and anticoagulation treatment is essential to prevent death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAtelectasis\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Efat embolism\u003C/strong\u003E are considered early complications, and typically present within 24-72 hours of the surgery/trauma. \u003Cstrong\u003EPneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E occurs as a result of unresolved atelectasis and presents around day 3 post-op. \u003Cstrong\u003EPneumothorax\u003C/strong\u003E is unlikely as there were no signs at the primary examination and the patient had been well leading up to this stage despite the rib fractures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A pulmonary embolus can be associated with few physical signs, yet still have serious consequences."],"references":["Miskovic A, Lumb AB, Postoperative pulmonary complications. Br. J. Anaesth. 2017;118(3):317-334. doi: 10.1093/bja/aex002","Tarbox AK, Swaroop M. Pulmonary embolism. Int J Crit Illn Inj Sci. 2013;3(1):69-72. doi:10.4103/2229-5151.109427","Abdelmaseeh TA, Azmat CE, Oliver TI. Postoperative Fever. [Updated 2020 Nov 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2020 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482299/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92015"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"786"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92015"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-23T15:05:42+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-23T15:06:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"786"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"109625"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":